	<presentation id="index">
		<title>Platform Economy: <br/>The Short Game and the Long Game</title>
		<toc class="abstract">API platforms are all the rage, and everybody wants to build a platform. However, often the communications on the business side focus on different aspects of a platform than they do on the IT side. In this presentation, we look at the superficial differences of platforms as they are referred to in the business and IT space, but more importantly, we also look at the deep underlying commonalities. Using these commonalities, we then analyze the economics of a platform that can justify the necessary investments. We identify the "platform short game" and the "platform long game", which allow to better understand how investment into a platform can yield quick results, but also how it can drive sustainable growth.</toc>
		<author><a href="http://dret.net/netdret/">Erik Wilde</a> <a href="http://twitter.com/dret" class="twitter-follow-button" data-size="large" title="Erik Wilde on Twitter: @dret">(<code>@dret</code>)</a></author>
