		<part id="your-platform">
			<title>You Have a Platform</title>
			<slide id="current-platform">
				<title>Your Current Platform</title>
				<ul>
					<li><em>Why</em> things are being built</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Customer focus</em> and improving their experience</li>
						<li><em>Innovation focus</em> and the ability to design/build/test/fail effectively</li>
					</ul>
					<li><em>What</em> you are building on</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Foundational resources</em> that serve as basic building blocks</li>
						<li><em>Existing capabilities</em> that can be reused in new value chains</li>
					</ul>
					<li><em>How</em> building things is working</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Design and build</em> support (getting from idea to implementation)</li>
						<li><em>Deployment and runtime</em> support (getting from implementation to operation)</li>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="platform-money-press">
				<title>The Platform Money Press</title>
				<img src="money-press.gif" style=" width : 90% ; height : 70% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 4% 0% 4% ; "/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="platform-recipe">
				<title>Tech &amp; Biz = Platform</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Platforms are what enable organization to create and deliver value</li>
					<li>Technology can be both limiting and enabling</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Limiting</em> when creation/delivery seems to be too slow/costly</li>
						<li><em>Enabling</em> when digitalization opens new opportunities</li>
					</ul>
					<li>Business can be both limiting and enabling</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Limiting</em> when business demands are not aligned with technology</li>
						<li><em>Enabling</em> when technology is used to create/deliver value faster</li>
					</ul>
					<li>Any platform must make sure to align technology and business</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
			<slide id="platform-pic">
				<title>Platforming: Building Products with a Plan</title>
				<img src="platform-perspectives.png" style=" width : 90% ; height : 70% ; object-fit : contain ; margin : 0% 4% 0% 4% ; "/>
			</slide>
			<slide id="paralysis">
				<title>Platform Paralysis</title>
				<ul>
					<li>Tech and Biz sometimes talk about platforms with a different focus</li>
					<ul>
						<li>The <em>Tech</em> view is focused on a technical set of capabilities</li>
						<li>The <em>Biz</em> view is focused on creating value by co-creation</li>
					</ul>
					<li>Platform success critically depends on aligning both views</li>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Tech</em> has to extend the focus to supporting value creation</li>
						<li><em>Biz</em> has to focus on grounding co-creation on the platform</li>
					</ul>
					<li>Define and align the goals and elements of the platform for all parties</li>
				</ul>
			</slide>
		</part>
		<part id="short-game">
			<title>Short Game: Grow the Platform</title>
			<slide id="foundation">
				<title>Growing the Foundation</title>
				<ul>
					<li><em href="https://www.apiscene.io/api-business-models/api-first-the-essence-of-digital-transformation/">API First</em> means to embrace APIs as the organization's business language</li>
					<li><em>API First</em> means making all assets/services available as APIs</li>
					<ol>
						<li>Expose existing/new <em>assets and capabilities</em> to the platform</li>
						<li>Add existing/new <em>experiences</em> to the platform</li>
					</ol>
				</ul>
			</slide>
